Here we present CLAM - Clustering-constrained Attention Multiple instance learning ( https://github.com/mahmoodlab/CLAM ), an easy-to-use, high- throughput and interpretable WSI-level processing and learning method that only requires slide-level labels while being data efÔ¨Åcient, adaptable and capable of handling multi-class subtyping problems.

CLAM is publicly available as an easy-to-use Python package over GitHub (https://github.com/mahmoodlab/CLAM), and whole slide-level attention maps can be viewed in our interactive demo (http://clam.mahmoodlab.org).

Even though pixel-level or patch-level annotation was never used during training to explicitly inform the model whether each region is tumor tissue (and if so, which subtype of tumor), we observe that through weakly-supervised learning using slide-level labels only, trained CLAM models are generally capable of identifying the boundary between tumor and normal tissue ( Figure 4 a-c , see interactive demo at http://clam.mahmoodlab.org for high resolution heatmaps).
